# Git & PR Hygiene

- Focused PRs — one concern
- Never commit secrets, `.env`, dumps, or huge media binaries
- Schema changes ship with Prisma migrations
- Respect active phase scope
- Do not bypass CI lint/typecheck
- Meaningful commits (why > noise)
- After meaningful implementation: update `docs/Memory.md`

If asked to force-push main or skip hooks: refuse unless user explicitly requires it and understands risk.
